            <title>[LU-14889] checksum_type support for server</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14889</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reported by Andreas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
one thing I noticed is that there are &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;{osc,mdc}.*.checksum_type files on the client, but there are no corresponding &quot;&lt;/span&gt;{mdt,ofd}.*.checksum_type&quot; files on the servers that report which checksum types are currently supported. It isn&apos;t possible to see &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; just from the client-side checksum_type because those may only list the fastest subset of types reported by the server.

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
